A two-thirds majority vote is needed in the 435-member House of Representatives and the 100-seat Senate, which appear able to strike down a Trump veto for the first time. The House is to vote to override Trump's veto on December 28, 2020 and Democrats are optimistic they have enough Republican support to do so. The Senate will take the matter up on December 29, 2020.
